External knowledge: 
- Quality scores are a measure of the reliability and accuracy of sensor data; 
- Cumulative quality scores represent the total quality score over time, while average quality scores provide a measure of the overall quality; 
- The query assumes that the quality check date is a reliable indicator of the order in which quality scores were obtained.

Sensor name refers to the unique identifier given to each sensor; 
Operational statuses include active, inactive, and maintenance; 
Average quality score is a measure of data reliability; 
Higher quality scores indicate more accurate sensor readings.
